1. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper deals with combinatorial theorems and Ramsey theory, which are topics in discrete mathematics. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper discusses the use of general-purpose complete and local-search techniques for testing propositional satisfiability, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the computational hardness of propositional theories and their use in benchmarking SAT solvers, which are topics in computational complexity. 
4. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper deals with propositional satisfiability and its use in representing combinatorial theorems, which are topics in logic in computer science. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the problem of computing van der Waerden numbers and the use of algorithms for testing propositional satisfiability, which are topics in data structures and algorithms.
